events.title: The Guardsmen Tree Lot Party
events.location: The Guardsmen Christmas Tree Lot, Festival Pavilion at the Fort Mason Center for Arts & Culture, San Francisco, CA 94123
events.description_preview: Celebrate the season with a magical night of dancing and beverages in an indoor winter wonderland.Th...
events.description_detail: Celebrate the season with a magical night of dancing and beverages in an indoor winter wonderland.The Guardsmen are excited to invite you to the party that San Francisco Magazine calls the "top holiday soiree" of the year.Enjoy a hosted bar from 8pmâ€“1:30am, dance, mingle and be jolly in what will be the best event of the holiday season!Chromeo (DJ Set) will be headlining The Guardsmen Tree Lot Party!Now almost twenty years into their storied career, Montreal natives Dave 1 and P-Thugg have turned an inseparable childhood friendship into a world-renowned, critically acclaimed marquee bandâ€”largely credited for pioneering the â€™80s-tinged electro-funk sound that permeates radio airwaves today. Chromeo are known for their analog synth sonics, catchy hooks, and iconic visuals, but also as a relentless touring actâ€”selling out shows internationally and regularly appearing on major festival stages. 2023 marked Chromeoâ€™s fifth performance at Coachella (theyâ€™ve also played Lollapalooza and Bonnaroo four times) and their seventh annual headline show at Coloradoâ€™s Red Rocks Amphitheater.Described as "THE party that everyone talks about for months", The Guardsmen Tree Lot Party brings together San Franciscoâ€™s glamorous and fun-loving partygoers, all to raise funds for over 2,500 Bay Area at-risk youth.The Festival Pavilion in Fort Mason Center is one of SF's most sensational waterfront venues and will be transformed into a winter wonderland that rivals the North Pole and will leave you awestruck. Beautiful Christmas trees line the entry as you make your way to your complimentary champagne. Have your picture taken with all your friends at the step and repeat or grab some fun snaps at one of the themed photo booths.Grab a drink from one of many bars, then make your way to one of the largest dance floors in all of San Francisco and enjoy the show.One of the most magical nights of the year is coming up.Be sure to get your ticket today!Cocktail Attire Strongly SuggestedA Huge Thank You To Our 2025 Tree Lot Sponsors:Presenting Sponsor: DiageoSnazzy BeveragesPlumpjack GroupBalboa CafeWhite RabbitAll proceeds benefit at-risk Bay Area kids: The Guardsmen make a life-changing difference in the lives of at-risk youth by raising funds for scholarships, camperships, and other youth programs. Learn more at www.guardsmen.orgFAQsWho are The Guardsmen? Why is this a benefit?Every year The Guardsmen changes lives across the Bay Area by sending more than 2,500 at-risk youth to outdoor education programs and by providing scholarships for more than 250 students to attend private schools. Learn more about The GuardsmenWhat should I wear?Cocktail attire is highly suggested. Because it is chilly in San Francisco, you can wear a jacket and leave it in our coat check while you enjoy the night's festivities. The event is held at The Guardsmen Christmas Tree Lot which sells living trees for weeks leading up to the event so, despite the well-swept floors, your shoes may get dirty.Do I need to bring money? Are drinks included?Drinks are included in all tickets. Please bring cash to tip. All tips and proceeds go to support Bay Area at-risk youth.Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?Per state law, guests must be 21 or older to attend; both scannable tickets and valid government ID's are required at the door for check-in - no exceptions.How should I get to the Tree Lot Party?Parking is limited at Fort Mason. Please consider taking a ride-sharing service.May I upgrade my ticket (e.g. GA to VIP)?Yes, please transfer to the other ticket type in Eventbrite. There will be the ability to upgrade your tickets at the venue.What does it take to put on The Guardsmen Tree Lot Party?The Tree Lot Party is put on entirely by volunteers. See this brief video on what it takes to put on this world-famous eventWhat's The Guardsmen's IRS status?The Guardsmen is a registered 501 (c) (3) nonprofit corporation. Donations are greatly appreciated and highly encouraged but are separate from ticket purchases. Only a ticket purchase grants the ticket holder entrance to the event. Separate donations alone can not qualify for entrance.What is the refund policy? How can I transfer my registration?While registrations are non-refundable, you may transfer your registration to a friend on Eventbrite.To learn about event sponsorship opportunities:Contact the event hosts with any questions: treelotparty@guardsmen.orgThank you for supporting The Guardsmen!guardsmen.orgRead moreCategory: Charity & Causes, Other
